article.headline: Nebraska 78, Alcorn St. 54
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. -- Lance Jeter scored 16 points and Jorge Brian Diaz added 15 as Nebraska rolled to a 78-57 victory over winless Alcorn State on Wednesday night. Brandon Ubel added 14 points on 6-of-7 shooting, Andre Almeida had 11 points and Caleb Walker grabbed 12 rebounds for the Cornhuskers (7-2). Marquiz Baker scored 32 points for Alcorn State, which dropped to 0-8. Nebraska took a 40-17 lead into halftime, snapping a recent streak of poor shooting performances in the opening half. Its 40 points were the most it had scored in the first half of a game this season. Alcorn State shot just 18.8 percent (6 of 32) in the first half before finishing at 29.7 percent overall.
